Delue, 1357, cited below, is probably to be associated with John Delvere, 1359 in   Colchester Court Rolls   (Essex)."]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":21,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":52,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":77,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":90,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":99,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh Delves was born in 1238, in Staffordshire, England. She had at least 1 son with Hugh DeDelves."},"et":{"1238–":"1238–Surnud","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1260–1281":"1260–1281","1285–1305":"1285–1305","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1238–Female":"1238–Surnud","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1260":"1260","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1238":"1238","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1453":"1453","1265":"1265","about 1265":"umbes 1265","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Doddington, Cheshire, England":"Doddington, Cheshire, England","Delves, Staffordshire, England":"Delves, Staffordshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1238–":"1238–Kuollut","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1260–1281":"1260–1281","1285–1305":"1285–1305","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1238–Female":"1238–Kuollut","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","1260":"1260","1281":"1281","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1238":"1238","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1453":"1453","1265":"1265","about 1265":"noin 1265","1328"